@startuml fig-tcp-handshake
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title TCP Connection Establishment (Three-Way Handshake)

participant "Client\n(ephemeral port)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server\n(well-known port)" as S #C8E6C9

note over C : CLOSED
note over S : LISTEN

C -[#1565C0]> S : SYN (Seq = x)
note over C : SYN-SENT

S -[#1565C0]> C : SYN-ACK (Seq = y, Ack = x + 1)
note over S : SYN-RECEIVED

C -[#43A047]> S : ACK (Seq = x + 1, Ack = y + 1)

== CONNECTION ESTABLISHED ==

note over C : ESTABLISHED
note over S : ESTABLISHED

C <-> S : Data transfer

legend right
  Step 1: Client sends SYN with initial Seq
  Step 2: Server replies SYN-ACK with its Seq
  Step 3: Client confirms with ACK
  Both sides exchange initial sequence
  numbers and negotiate TCP options
  (MSS, SACK, window scale).
endlegend
@enduml
